newsitem.title: UK: NWE naphtha ends steady to lower in sleepy trade.
newsitem.headline: NWE naphtha ends steady to lower in sleepy trade.

text.p: NWE naphtha prices ended steady to lower in quiet trade due to holidays across Europe and a generally balanced market, traders said.
Stronger gasoline prices and seasonal factors are buoying heavier naphthenic and aromatic material, they said, but end-user demand is generally lacklustre.
May swaps ended down $1 at $180.50/$181.50 a tonne with June at $183/$184 and July at $183.50/$184.50.
Cargoes were notionally assessed at $180/$182 cif.
